36:41.116 --> 36:44.577
Kids. What's the big deal?

36:44.661 --> 36:46.245
Do you want to have kids?

36:47.789 --> 36:49.915
Eventually.

36:50.000 --> 36:51.458
Exactly.

37:02.596 --> 37:04.763
Mr. Romano, Miss Olson.

37:06.266 --> 37:07.600
Send them in.

37:09.978 --> 37:11.312
Where are we?

37:11.396 --> 37:13.230
You tell us.

37:15.609 --> 37:17.610
"Where are you going?"

37:19.654 --> 37:21.530
Are you going to underline the "you"?

37:21.615 --> 37:23.407
For half the people, it will be,

37:23.491 --> 37:25.367
"Where are you going?"

37:25.452 --> 37:28.370
I also had "Come away with us."

37:30.290 --> 37:31.498
Where the hell's Dale?

37:32.751 --> 37:34.335
He's sick.

37:36.421 --> 37:38.088
I don't know. Sure.

37:38.173 --> 37:39.381
Fine.

37:39.466 --> 37:41.342
It's exactly what we talked about.

37:41.426 --> 37:43.010
It's obvious.

37:44.262 --> 37:46.013
I'm uninvolνed.

37:55.190 --> 37:56.523
Move this up.

37:59.444 --> 38:01.028
What about that?

38:03.907 --> 38:05.157
I think it's sentimental.

38:05.283 --> 38:06.617
Peggy.

38:06.701 --> 38:09.244
No, she's right.

38:09.329 --> 38:13.749
Just because it has sentiment
doesn't make it sentimental.

38:13.833 --> 38:15.501
We're talking about businessmen.

38:15.585 --> 38:19.046
Right. Businessmen
who like short skirts.

38:19.130 --> 38:20.464
Sex sells.

38:23.468 --> 38:24.885
Says who?

38:30.642 --> 38:31.725
Just so you know,

38:31.810 --> 38:37.064
the people who talk that way
think that monkeys can do this.

38:37.148 --> 38:40.150
And they take all this monkey crap
and just stick it in a briefcase,

38:40.235 --> 38:42.611
completely unaware that their success

38:42.696 --> 38:45.406
depends on something
more than their shoe shine.

38:54.416 --> 38:57.418
You are the product.

38:57.502 --> 39:00.671
You feeling something.

39:00.755 --> 39:02.423
That's what sells.

39:02.507 --> 39:04.800
Not them.

39:04.884 --> 39:07.052
Not sex.

39:11.057 --> 39:13.267
They can't do what we do.

39:13.351 --> 39:15.352
And they hate us for it.

39:23.737 --> 39:26.321
"Welcome back, Daddy"?

39:26.406 --> 39:27.740
Is that a question?

39:32.412 --> 39:35.289
"What did you bring me, Daddy?"

39:43.757 --> 39:45.758
You can put that in your book.

40:05.111 --> 40:06.987
What is going on?

40:34.224 --> 40:36.391
He's going to take it to Leon in Actuarial?

40:36.476 --> 40:39.603
His stomach's so fat,
it's now resting on his desk.

40:39.687 --> 40:41.980
Got to feed that big brain.

40:42.065 --> 40:44.399
He's a deal breaker.

40:44.484 --> 40:46.360
I'm a closer.

40:47.445 --> 40:48.570
That Cecelia?

40:48.655 --> 40:50.072
Sits outside Fred Talbot's office?

40:50.156 --> 40:51.865
You made that happen?

40:51.950 --> 40:53.033
Silver tongue.

40:57.664 --> 40:59.414
I got her three stingers.

40:59.499 --> 41:00.749
She's a little girl.

41:00.834 --> 41:02.543
You have to give them an excuse.

41:02.627 --> 41:03.752
That's what I always say.

41:03.837 --> 41:05.963
She had those panties
that said "Wednesday."

41:06.047 --> 41:07.214
They were soaked through.

41:07.298 --> 41:08.590
I loνe that.

41:08.675 --> 41:10.134
Once the engine was running,

41:10.218 --> 41:11.343
she wouldn't stop.

41:11.469 --> 41:12.845
She's so straight.

41:12.929 --> 41:14.179
You'd think that.

41:15.849 --> 41:17.307
Take your hat off.

41:19.811 --> 41:21.520
Is there a problem?

41:57.223 --> 41:58.891
Damn it.

42:14.407 --> 42:16.116
Everything okay?

42:16.201 --> 42:18.160
You know anything about cars?

42:18.244 --> 42:19.745
No.

42:21.039 --> 42:23.957
Can you tell them at the Esso
to send a tow truck?

42:24.042 --> 42:25.375
Okay.

42:37.388 --> 42:38.805
Hey, Carla.

42:38.890 --> 42:40.599
Hi.

42:41.935 --> 42:43.810
Hey, Daddy.

42:43.895 --> 42:45.437
How was your day, Mr. Draper?

42:46.564 --> 42:48.774
I am tired.

42:48.858 --> 42:50.025
Where's Mrs. Draper?

42:50.109 --> 42:52.778
She just went to get Sally from ballet.

42:53.947 --> 42:55.739
Want a ride to the station?

42:55.823 --> 42:58.659
No. l'm all right.

42:58.743 --> 43:01.036
It's a nice night out. l enjoy the fresh air.

43:01.120 --> 43:02.537
Good night, Bobby.

43:02.622 --> 43:05.290
Good night.

43:13.591 --> 43:15.634
I don't like it.

43:19.013 --> 43:21.807
Here. Give it to me.

43:28.648 --> 43:30.649
I just know when the smoke
starts to come out,

43:30.733 --> 43:32.359
I have to stop.

43:32.443 --> 43:33.568
That's true.

43:33.653 --> 43:37.656
I got a fan belt on the truck.
I could put it in for $9.00.

43:38.741 --> 43:40.117
Hold on.

44:04.142 --> 44:05.809
I have $3.00 and change.

44:05.893 --> 44:07.644
I could put it on account,

44:07.729 --> 44:09.062
send you a bill.

44:09.147 --> 44:10.814
I don't want my husband
knowing about this.

44:10.898 --> 44:12.149
It's a new car.

44:12.233 --> 44:14.735
He doesn't like the way l driνe.

44:14.819 --> 44:16.695
That's got nothing to do with this.

44:21.409 --> 44:24.786
Well, it would mean the world to me.

44:24.871 --> 44:26.663
I don't know. You know, the--

44:26.748 --> 44:29.374
the belt's 2.55.

44:30.668 --> 44:35.380
So there's nothing you can do
for a damsel in distress?

44:38.968 --> 44:41.219
Are we bargaining here?

44:42.930 --> 44:47.642
Well, yes, I guess we are.

44:47.727 --> 44:50.562
I could say no, couldn't l?

44:52.106 --> 44:54.691
That would be
a terrible disappointment.

44:54.776 --> 44:57.110
It would be, wouldn't it?

45:26.933 --> 45:28.558
It's not that complicated.

45:28.643 --> 45:30.310
That's a relief.

45:43.241 --> 45:46.785
Well, that'll do it.

45:59.006 --> 46:00.966
Have a good night now.

46:01.050 --> 46:04.136
I will.

46:14.355 --> 46:15.939
Polly!

46:18.526 --> 46:19.651
I'm here, too.

46:19.777 --> 46:20.819
Hi, Daddy.

46:20.903 --> 46:22.154
Hi.

46:24.615 --> 46:25.907
Bobby conked out.

46:25.992 --> 46:27.367
Where were you?

46:27.452 --> 46:28.743
Mommy was late.

46:28.828 --> 46:33.248
I got stuck talking to Marilyn Keckner
in the parking lot.

46:33.332 --> 46:35.584
Well, I was here.

46:35.668 --> 46:36.960
Did you eat something?

46:37.044 --> 46:38.170
I did.

46:40.006 --> 46:42.507
Come on, show me
what you learned in ballet.

47:04.113 --> 47:05.655
Now l am quietly waiting

47:05.740 --> 47:07.616
for the catastrophe of my personality

47:07.700 --> 47:09.826
to seem beautiful again,

47:09.911 --> 47:12.704
and interesting and modern.

47:20.254 --> 47:21.963
The country is gray

47:22.048 --> 47:25.842
and brown and white and trees.

47:28.304 --> 47:32.390
Snows and skies of laughter
are always diminishing.

47:32.475 --> 47:35.018
Less funny, not just darker.

47:35.102 --> 47:37.145
Not just gray.

47:38.856 --> 47:42.067
It may be the coldest day of the year.

47:42.151 --> 47:44.945
What does he think of that?

47:45.029 --> 47:48.156
I mean, what do I?

47:49.492 --> 47:51.576
And if I do,

47:51.661 --> 47:55.622
perhaps I am myself again.

